'''Scamander Vallis''' is an ancient river valley in the [[Amenthes quadrangle]] of Mars, located at 16 North and 331.5 West.  It is 204 km long and was named after an ancient name of a river at Troy (modern Turkey).<ref>http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/</ref> 
<gallery>
Image:Scamander Vallis.JPG|[[Scamander Vallis]], as seen by [[HiRISE]].  Click on image to see [[Dark Slope Streaks]] in a variety of shades.  The darker the streak the younger it is.  Scale bar is 500 meters long.
  
</gallery>

